[[cdo:9 nguŏk 9 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:9 goe̍h 9 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:九月初九]] {{Lunisolar September}} '''September 9''' is the 9th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September|12=draft}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|12=draft}} .
== Events == * Year 4 of {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft}} (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 22|ja|10月22日|12=draft}} , [[1871]] ) – The "Noon Cannon System" ({{ill|午砲の制}} ) was enacted, establishing the practice of firing a cannon at noon from the former main keep of {{ill|Edo Castle|ja|江戸城|12=draft}} to signal the time.
== Births == * Year 13 of {{ill|Hōreki|ja|Hōreki|12=draft}} (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 15|ja|10月15日|12=draft}} , [[1763]] ) – {{ill|Tani Bunchō|ja|谷文晁|12=draft}} , {{ill|painter|ja|Painter|12=draft}} (d. [[1841]] ). * Year 1 of {{ill|Kyōwa|ja|享和|12=draft}} (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|12=draft}} , [[1801]] ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Saijun|ja|徳川斉順|12=draft}} , 11th {{ill|Daimyō|ja|大名|12=draft}} of {{ill|Kishū Domain|ja|紀州藩|12=draft}} (d. [[1846]] ). * Year 11 of {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft}} (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 17|ja|10月17日|12=draft}} , [[1828]] ) – {{ill|Soejima Taneomi|ja|副島種臣|12=draft}} , {{ill|Minister of Foreign Affairs (Japan)|ja|外務卿|12=draft}} and Minister of Home Affairs (d. [[1905]] ). * Year 3 of {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft}} (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 6|ja|10月6日|12=draft}} , [[1867]] ) – {{ill|Hirayama Shin|ja|平山信|12=draft}} , {{ill|astronomer|ja|天文学者|12=draft}} (d. [[1945]] ).
== Deaths == * Year 1 of {{ill|Shuchō|ja|朱鳥|12=draft}} (Julian calendar {{ill|October 1|ja|10月1日|12=draft}} , [[686]] ) – {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|12=draft}} , 40th emperor of Japan. * Year 5 of {{ill|Jitō|ja|Empress Jitō|12=draft}} (Julian calendar {{ill|October 6|ja|10月6日|12=draft}} , [[691]] ) – {{ill|Prince Kawashima|ja|川島皇子|12=draft}} , Japanese imperial prince (b. [[657]] ). * Year 1 of {{ill|Eishō|ja|永正|12=draft}} (Julian calendar {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|12=draft}} , [[1504]] ) – {{ill|Mogami Yoshizumi|ja|最上義淳|12=draft}} , {{ill|Sengoku daimyō|ja|戦国大名|12=draft}} . * Year 14 of {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft}} (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 21|ja|10月21日|12=draft}} , [[1586]] ) – {{ill|Takikawa Kazumasu|ja|滝川一益|12=draft}} , samurai commander (b. [[1525]] ).
== Commemorations == * {{ill|Chōyō Festival|ja|重陽|12=draft}} Festival. ** *Kiku-no-sake* (菊御酒, *Chikūjakī*) – In {{ill|Okinawa Prefecture|ja|沖縄県|12=draft}} , sake with floating chrysanthemum petals is offered to household altars and fire gods to pray for family safety. * Senior Citizens' Day ({{CHN}} , {{lang-zh|老年节}} ) – Defined in Article 9 of the {{ill|PRC Elderly Rights Protection Law|ja|中華人民共和国老年人権益保障法|12=draft}} .<ref name="jil">{{Cite web|和書|url=http://www.jil.go.jp/foreign/jihou/2013_7/china_05.html|title=「高齢者権益保障法」が7月に施行―「喜憂半々」の受け止め、期待と不安と|date=2013-07|publisher={{ill|Japan Institute for Labour Policy and Training|ja|労働政策研究・研修機構|12=draft}} |accessdate=2016-01-17|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117131729/http://www.jil.go.jp/foreign/jihou/2013_7/china_05.html|archivedate=2016-01-17}} </ref> * {{ill|Kugatsukunchi|ja|クガツクンチ|12=draft}} , celebrated in the {{ill|Amami Islands|ja|奄美群島|12=draft}} .
