'''September 9''' is the 9th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} . 
== Events ==
* Year 4 of {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 22|ja|10月22日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , [[1871]] ) – The "Noon Cannon System" ({{ill|午砲の制|qq=}} ) was enacted, establishing the practice of firing a cannon at noon from the former main keep of {{ill|Edo Castle|ja|江戸城|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  to signal the time.

== Births ==
* Year 13 of {{ill|Hōreki|ja|Hōreki|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 15|ja|10月15日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , [[1763]] ) – {{ill|Tani Bunchō|ja|谷文晁|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , {{ill|painter|ja|Painter|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (d. [[1841]] ).
* Year 1 of {{ill|Kyōwa|ja|享和|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , [[1801]] ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Saijun|ja|徳川斉順|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , 11th {{ill|Daimyō|ja|大名|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  of {{ill|Kishū Domain|ja|紀州藩|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (d. [[1846]] ).
* Year 11 of {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 17|ja|10月17日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , [[1828]] ) – {{ill|Soejima Taneomi|ja|副島種臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , {{ill|Minister of Foreign Affairs (Japan)|ja|外務卿|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  and Minister of Home Affairs (d. [[1905]] ).
* Year 3 of {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 6|ja|10月6日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , [[1867]] ) – {{ill|Hirayama Shin|ja|平山信|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , {{ill|astronomer|ja|天文学者|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (d. [[1945]] ).

== Deaths ==
* Year 1 of {{ill|Shuchō|ja|朱鳥|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (Julian calendar {{ill|October 1|ja|10月1日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , [[686]] ) – {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , 40th emperor of Japan.
* Year 5 of {{ill|Jitō|ja|Empress Jitō|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (Julian calendar {{ill|October 6|ja|10月6日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , [[691]] ) – {{ill|Prince Kawashima|ja|川島皇子|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , Japanese imperial prince (b. [[657]] ).
* Year 1 of {{ill|Eishō|ja|永正|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (Julian calendar {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , [[1504]] ) – {{ill|Mogami Yoshizumi|ja|最上義淳|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , {{ill|Sengoku daimyō|ja|戦国大名|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} .
* Year 14 of {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  (Gregorian calendar {{ill|October 21|ja|10月21日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , [[1586]] ) – {{ill|Takikawa Kazumasu|ja|滝川一益|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , samurai commander (b. [[1525]] ).

